There are two types of accounts in thinkParity. A 'Guest' account is free. A standard account gives you the ability to collaborate with guests and invite them to use thinkParity for free.

For more information about account types see www.thinkParity.com/pricing.

To upgrade from a guest account to a standard account, press the 'Upgrade' button at the top of thinkParity and follow the instructions in the upgrade wizard.

<p>If you have a standard thinkParity account then you can change the credit card that you use to pay for thinkParity. To change account information, click your name located in the bottom right of thinkParity, then press the 'Manage Account' button.

To view the license agreement, press the 'Manage Account' button and then click the license agreement link on the dialog.